# BodaSure Scalability, Anti-Over-Engineering, & Portal Layout Laws

## High-Scale Performance (100,000+ Users)
- **Database footprints:** Write queries keeping high concurrency in mind. Never loop queries inside frontend components. Always leverage optimized indexes and database-level filters inside Supabase to minimize payload size.
- **Avoid N+1 Query Pitfalls:** All lists, dashboards, and feeds must fetch nested relationships via single, optimized database queries or joins rather than multiple staggered network requests.

## Anti-Over-Engineering (KISS/YAGNI)
- Keep solutions highly focused, lightweight, and modular. Do not introduce speculative software architectures, unnecessary wrappers, or complex multi-layered abstractions. Write clean, readable React and TypeScript code that an intermediate developer can pick up immediately.

## Portal & Device Optimization Layouts
- **Mobile-First Core Portals:** The **Rider App (/app)**, **Owner workflows**, and **Field Agent (/agent)** modules are strictly mobile-first. UI structures must be optimized for mid-to-low-tier mobile screens commonly used in Kenya, focusing on large touch targets, low data overhead, and zero side-scrolling.
- **Desktop but Mobile Optimized Admin Portals:** The **SACCO (/sacco)** and **Super Admin (/admin)** portals are data-dense environments built for desktop layouts but also mobile optimized. Prioritize responsive, clean, modern shadcn/ui data tables, clear metric cards, and split-pane analytics layouts.

## Interconnected Data Integrity
- Ensure state mutations flow reactively across all 7 portals via Supabase Realtime hooks. For example: If a rider initiates a payment event or triggers a compliance check inside the Rider App, that state must immediately update the corresponding SACCO monitoring feed and the Super Admin ledger without requiring a manual page refresh.
